The article highlights the special guests who joined President Donald J. Trump and First Lady Melania Trump for the President's third State of the Union address. The guests come from various backgrounds and represent the best of America. Some of the notable guests include Janiyah Davis, a 4th-grade student from Philadelphia who received a scholarship to attend a school of her choice, Juan Guaido, the Interim President of Venezuela and leader of the democratically elected Venezuelan National Assembly, Kelli and Gage Hake, who suffered from the actions of Iranian terrorist leader Qasem Soleimani, Jody Jones, whose brother was killed by an illegal immigrant due to California's sanctuary state policy, Rush Limbaugh, a legendary radio host who was awarded the Presidential Medal of Freedom, and retired Brigadier General Charles McGee, a Tuskegee Airman and veteran of World War II, the Korean War, and the Vietnam War. Other guests include a veteran, a family whose daughter was kidnapped and murdered by ISIS, a Deputy Chief of U.S. Border Patrol, a former soldier who overcame addiction and reunited with his family, parents of a premature baby who survived against the odds, a former Chief of Police from Venezuela, a brother who lost his sibling to suicide, and a military spouse and mother of two.